review: I cannot bring myself to give Jane Austen a “meh” star rating. I just can’t. However, “meh” is my feeling about Mansfield Park. I read it for the firsI cannot bring myself to give Jane Austen a “meh” star rating. I just can’t. However, “meh” is my feeling about Mansfield Park. I read it for the first time in university and didn’t get it. I went in with reasonably high expectations because I enjoyed the 1999 film adaptation and then I felt cheated. This reread does not do much to shift my feelings about this one. It’s Fanny people, she’s the centre of my struggles with MP. I want her to be more, and she just isn’t. I get that this is sort of the point of Fanny, and yet she disappoints me.So, I put down this book glad it is over, which sort of breaks my heart as an Austenite. I have decided to seek out the opinions and insights of Austen scholars on MP, so that I might shift my view before the next time I decide to reread all of Austen.In the meantime, there are still some lovely lines to savor, thank goodness…Lines I underlined:“Life seems but a quick succession of busy nothings.”“We have all a better guide in ourselves, if we would attend to it, than any other person can be.”“But indeed I would rather have nothing but tea.”“I have no talent for certainty.”...more
